CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 27, 1957, pg. 3, reads: "Juvenile Jury Observes - Although they wern't [weren't] able to 'make' the Easter parade themselves, it did not prevent this happy 'juvenile jury' from turning out to watch members of the 'lollipop set' and elder 'fashion plates' display their finery going to and from church."
TitMainTitle: Ten children, possibly including Barbara Nickens second from left, Peggy Nickens, Kenny Nickens, unknown, Ginger Patterson, Darnell Patterson, Ralph "PeeWee" Patterson, and two unknown girls, seated on Miller High Life billboard with image of woman
